# Commit-msg hook — enforces Conventional Commits format.
#
# Every commit message must match:
#   <type>(<scope>): <sentence>
#
# e.g. fix(sms): partial-delivery reporting shows carrier status per number
#
# Rules live in commitlint.config.cjs at repo root. Bypassing this with
# --no-verify is explicitly against the H1.5 team agreement — if a commit
# message is getting rejected, rewrite it, don't skip the hook.
#
# The $1 argument is the path to the .git/COMMIT_EDITMSG file husky passes
# us; commitlint reads it with --edit.

npx --no-install commitlint --edit "$1"
